1
00:00:28,567 --> 00:00:54,962
so good afternoon everybody so I hope you're ready for to do a little bit of that meta practice so if you get yourself into a good meditational posture I'll go through an explanation and then we'll do the exercise and the exercise includes after meta the forgiveness exercise and then how to develop our sense of determination okay

2
00:01:20,085 --> 00:01:27,474
By the way, this morning, those of you who opened your eyes and looked at the screen may have noticed that I was leaning to the left.

3
00:01:28,456 --> 00:01:29,075
Oops, something like that.

4
00:01:30,737 --> 00:01:31,478
I didn't used to.

5
00:01:31,498 --> 00:01:34,903
I think this is to do with some injury I have in the spine.

6
00:01:34,962 --> 00:01:37,045
I've got a prolapsed disc on one side.

7
00:01:37,686 --> 00:01:38,908
And I think that's what makes me do it.

8
00:01:39,308 --> 00:01:40,588
I'm not aware of it at all.

9
00:01:40,930 --> 00:01:42,712
See, just like the leaning tarapisa.

10
00:01:43,171 --> 00:01:44,453
I'm not aware I'm leaning.

11
00:01:46,256 --> 00:01:49,840
So let's get ourselves into a...

12
00:01:50,072 --> 00:02:13,683
comfortable posture so the usual thing make sure the energy is running up the spine lifting up from the lower back and the abdomen just a moment to relax the brow jaw the shoulders and

13
00:02:36,192 --> 00:02:40,176
So let me explain a few things about metta before we actually do the practice.

14
00:02:41,457 --> 00:02:48,466
Remember that when we are practicing vipassana, the quality that we want to develop is equanimity.

15
00:02:50,008 --> 00:02:55,993
So there's no specific effort to develop goodwill or compassion or joy.

16
00:02:56,055 --> 00:02:58,858
In a sense, that's all presumed.

17
00:02:59,739 --> 00:03:02,622
We wouldn't be doing it were it not that we care for ourselves.

18
00:03:04,474 --> 00:03:16,213
But when we finish the Vipassana and come out into the world, that equanimity can stay with us and can begin to corrupt into what's known as its more subtle enemy of indifference.

19
00:03:16,234 --> 00:03:18,717
We might feel we're not engaging.

20
00:03:20,241 --> 00:03:22,544
People might feel that we are indifferent.

21
00:03:23,825 --> 00:03:26,951
And so the way we overcome that is by practicing metta.

22
00:03:27,051 --> 00:03:28,473
That re-engages us.

23
00:03:29,973 --> 00:03:36,526
Now metta is the basic relationship that the Buddha put to us that we should have towards all beings.

24
00:03:37,127 --> 00:03:49,469
So sometimes it's translated as an affective feeling of loving kindness, but I much prefer an attitudinal way of looking at it.

25
00:03:49,530 --> 00:03:51,112
In other words, goodwill.

26
00:03:51,614 --> 00:03:52,977
It's just goodwill.

27
00:03:53,901 --> 00:04:20,415
and these lead now when you've established a good relationship of goodwill with everybody but I mean it's easy to do with friends obviously you can see that if a friend or a family member or whatever falls into misfortune there's just a natural desire to help and if they fall if they have a good fortune then of course you're happy for them so

28
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:28,067
compassion and empathetic joy arise quite naturally from that base of goodwill.

29
00:04:30,649 --> 00:04:41,422
Now when we talk about it being non-attached, in the old books you might read detached, which sounded a very cold sort of love or goodwill.

30
00:04:42,262 --> 00:04:47,908
Now they use this non-dual term, neither attached nor detached, but non-attached.

31
00:04:47,928 --> 00:04:49,170
But I think we can...

32
00:04:49,639 --> 00:04:52,182
say, simply universal.

33
00:04:52,944 --> 00:04:59,011
It rises above whether we like somebody or not, or whether they like us or not.

34
00:04:59,672 --> 00:05:04,716
So it's rising above personality to the humanity within us.

35
00:05:04,817 --> 00:05:09,322
And of course, this can be extended to any living being, all animals.

36
00:05:11,665 --> 00:05:17,351
Now, it's not an emotion per se, but an attitude, as I say.

37
00:05:17,533 --> 00:05:40,487
so don't worry if you don't feel loving it's still working because these intentions are creating a habit right from an intention you get an action an action of thought in this case and an action of uh which comes out of goodwill and from that you get a habit

38
00:05:40,720 --> 00:05:45,387
So don't worry about whether you feel like practicing metta or not.

39
00:05:46,389 --> 00:05:48,033
The heart may respond.

40
00:05:48,153 --> 00:05:52,519
You might have lovely warm feelings and there's no problem with that at all.

41
00:05:52,821 --> 00:06:05,562
And in fact, you might, as you say, encourage the heart by sending warm feelings from the heart to the various subjects that we bring to mind.

42
00:06:08,935 --> 00:06:10,516
So just practice anyway.

43
00:06:12,418 --> 00:06:20,204
So the practice, we go through the various categories, as you'll see.

44
00:06:20,745 --> 00:06:23,208
First particular and then more universal.

45
00:06:23,648 --> 00:06:27,072
And when we get to all beings, we'll do it in the six directions.

46
00:06:27,612 --> 00:06:31,235
All beings before us, behind us, left, right, above and below.

47
00:06:31,274 --> 00:06:36,120
Now, the traditional blessings, if you wish to use them.

48
00:06:36,519 --> 00:06:38,401
And of course, you can always make up your own.

49
00:06:38,973 --> 00:06:43,737
But the traditional blessings are, may you be safe, well and happy.

50
00:06:43,757 --> 00:06:46,519
Everybody wants to be safe.

51
00:06:46,658 --> 00:06:47,839
Everybody wants good health.

52
00:06:48,341 --> 00:06:51,423
And of course, everybody wants to be free of mental distress.

53
00:06:52,124 --> 00:06:54,586
So may you be safe, well and happy.

54
00:06:55,387 --> 00:06:58,769
And to have a certain ease about living.

55
00:06:59,370 --> 00:07:06,935
So to live contented and in harmony with the world, even when the world is not such a pleasant place for us.

56
00:07:07,557 --> 00:07:08,877
So to live contented

57
00:07:09,247 --> 00:07:37,565
in harmony with the world so as may you be well safe well and happy live contented in harmony with the world so let's begin by bringing to mind someone who's been a benefactor for us someone who's helped us in our lives and as you picture that person in your mind's eye

58
00:07:37,899 --> 00:07:43,514
Just drive your goodwill towards them.

59
00:07:43,535 --> 00:07:46,682
May you be safe, well and happy.

60
00:07:50,452 --> 00:07:54,423
May you live contented in harmony with the world.

61
00:08:16,543 --> 00:08:23,139
We can bring to mind someone who is near and dear to us, or more than someone, it doesn't matter.

62
00:08:27,168 --> 00:08:32,881
And again, as you picture them in your mind's eye, just drive your goodwill towards them.

63
00:09:16,484 --> 00:09:18,029
You can bring to mind a friend.

64
00:09:22,750 --> 00:09:24,115
Even an acquaintance.

65
00:10:09,758 --> 00:10:12,162
Now there's a category of a neutral person.

66
00:10:12,322 --> 00:10:20,716
So if you think about it, many days in our lives, we see many tens of people whom we don't know.

67
00:10:21,618 --> 00:10:23,321
These are all neutral people.

68
00:10:24,081 --> 00:10:32,716
Can you think of somebody whom you see quite often when you travel, maybe at work, just down the street, a neighbour, but you don't know them?

69
00:10:34,119 --> 00:10:36,221
Offer them the same quality of goodwill.

70
00:11:16,346 --> 00:11:19,750
Turning now that stream of goodwill towards ourselves.

71
00:11:20,171 --> 00:11:28,119
Now, if you find that's difficult, if you're suffering a little bit from self-aversion, just put that to the side.

72
00:11:28,339 --> 00:11:29,640
So we're not suppressing it.

73
00:11:29,941 --> 00:11:30,721
We know it's there.

74
00:11:31,503 --> 00:11:38,210
When we suppress something, we do it with anger or with aversion, shall we say, or fear.

75
00:11:38,929 --> 00:11:43,434
But here we just acknowledge it, just putting it to the side, parking it,

76
00:11:43,549 --> 00:11:52,168
Sometimes it helps to put your hand over your heart and then just speak gently into your own heart.

77
00:11:52,187 --> 00:11:54,852
May I be safe, well and happy.

78
00:11:56,076 --> 00:12:00,124
May I live contented in harmony with the world.

79
00:12:38,191 --> 00:12:43,780
Now it's at this point that we can bring somebody into the heart who we're having a hard time with.

80
00:12:44,461 --> 00:12:46,706
So obviously you don't have to go for the big one.

81
00:12:47,707 --> 00:12:51,754
Just make it somebody who you don't feel too bad about.

82
00:12:52,697 --> 00:13:01,633
And just as they sort of slip into your mind, just hold them there for a second and just at least offer them your goodwill.

83
00:13:48,172 --> 00:13:51,095
Now we can open up more outwardly.

84
00:13:51,134 --> 00:13:59,542
Now, if there are other people living with you in the house, then we bring them in now.

85
00:14:00,403 --> 00:14:08,830
For those who are living, shall we say, with close neighbours in flats or something, you can bring those people in.

86
00:14:10,131 --> 00:14:16,136
Whoever is around you, just bring them into your metta, into your goodwill,

87
00:14:16,909 --> 00:14:18,515
and offer them your blessings.

88
00:15:00,126 --> 00:15:12,263
And from there, just begin to widen out to include your neighborhood, your village, your small town, just the wider area in which you live.

89
00:15:54,092 --> 00:15:57,792
And from there, radiating out to all the people in our country

90
00:16:48,076 --> 00:16:57,342
And from there to all the peoples of Europe, if you happen to be in another continent, of course, to all the peoples of your continent.

91
00:17:42,936 --> 00:17:45,910
and from there to all people on earth.

92
00:18:32,042 --> 00:18:35,167
So now we come to all beings in all directions.

93
00:18:36,329 --> 00:18:44,362
So here you can just think of it as infinite space and just send out your goodwill in all directions.

94
00:18:46,705 --> 00:18:59,265
I mean if you have a vivid imagination you might populate them but I think it's just enough just to send your goodwill into a sort of infinite space.

95
00:19:00,882 --> 00:19:03,146
all beings before us.

96
00:19:49,903 --> 00:19:52,606
all beings behind us.

97
00:20:35,955 --> 00:20:38,202
All beings to our left.

98
00:21:23,813 --> 00:21:26,179
all beings to our right.

99
00:22:09,105 --> 00:22:11,808
all beings below us

100
00:22:54,432 --> 00:22:56,763
All beings above us.

101
00:23:44,467 --> 00:23:48,942
And finally, to all beings in all directions.

102
00:24:37,488 --> 00:24:46,241
Having developed our goodwill, we can move into the area of forgivingness, overcoming our grudges and our resentments.

103
00:24:47,644 --> 00:24:49,026
So there are three areas.

104
00:24:49,267 --> 00:24:55,916
There is asking for forgiveness, forgiving others and forgiving ourselves.

105
00:25:00,203 --> 00:25:02,887
So beginning with asking for forgiveness.

106
00:25:04,993 --> 00:25:07,518
Can we bring to mind someone whom we've hurt?

107
00:25:08,660 --> 00:25:10,762
And again, we don't have to go for the big one.

108
00:25:12,105 --> 00:25:16,090
This is an exercise which we can extend in the fullness of time.

109
00:25:16,971 --> 00:25:21,779
If you can bring to mind somebody whom you've hurt in some way, a sharp word or whatever.

110
00:25:26,066 --> 00:25:33,718
Now, as they come to mind, you'll find you have a memory of an event or the person themselves.

111
00:25:34,778 --> 00:26:03,991
and the attitude will come of hurting them and you may find there still justifying yourself or you might find some guilt or some shame or a desire to be reconciled remorse so it's a case of using this image this event to contact those feelings and to really allow them to express themselves now you have to be very careful

112
00:26:04,259 --> 00:26:09,946
not to let this image or this memory suddenly draw you into a fantasy.

113
00:26:10,968 --> 00:26:15,575
In which case, of course, it will be developing one of these attitudes.

114
00:26:15,595 --> 00:26:16,655
So be careful of that.

115
00:26:17,237 --> 00:26:29,314
You have to hold the event, hold the person in your mind, and as it were, look into your heart and just see if you can feel what your reaction is.

116
00:26:30,415 --> 00:26:32,898
Is there still some justification there?

117
00:26:33,317 --> 00:26:36,647
Is there still guilt or shame, sense of remorse?

118
00:26:37,089 --> 00:26:38,192
And just stay with it.

119
00:26:38,755 --> 00:26:40,842
Just let the heart express itself.

120
00:26:42,768 --> 00:26:44,172
Someone whom we hurt.

121
00:27:08,434 --> 00:27:35,099
can we see how we've hurt ourselves how these mental states are unwholesome unskillful knowing that they will just create more suffering

122
00:27:35,434 --> 00:27:39,426
We undermine them by seeking reconciliation.

123
00:27:41,594 --> 00:27:49,376
So again, we bring that person to mind and talk to them and bring yourself round to apologising, to make amends.

124
00:28:16,761 --> 00:28:21,669
Perhaps you can see in them a desire to be reconciled, holding out a hand of friendship.

125
00:28:24,592 --> 00:28:25,374
Can you take it?

126
00:28:37,529 --> 00:28:39,192
Allowing the love back in.

127
00:29:01,260 --> 00:29:03,163
And let's offer them our good wishes.

128
00:29:23,355 --> 00:29:25,377
Allowing them to fade away.

129
00:29:33,931 --> 00:29:37,634
Well, you can see here the two purposes for such an exercise.

130
00:29:37,734 --> 00:29:40,837
First of all, it's a process of healing the heart.

131
00:29:41,478 --> 00:29:44,401
It's also just like we go for an interview for a job.

132
00:29:44,421 --> 00:29:47,344
You're preparing yourself for that interview.

133
00:29:47,364 --> 00:29:57,553
And even though the interview is nothing like the way you would imagine it, what you have done is prepared yourself and entered the room with a certain confidence.

134
00:29:58,314 --> 00:30:00,115
So it is with these exercises.

135
00:30:00,276 --> 00:30:03,499
It makes it more easy for us to ask for forgiveness.

136
00:30:06,247 --> 00:30:33,147
turning now to somebody who's hurt us so again don't feel you have to go for the big one and as that person comes to mind there'll be an event or there might be a history and of course we'll have hurt and we tend not to want to feel the hurt it's humiliating after all we prefer to be angry and to seek revenge

137
00:30:33,532 --> 00:30:43,005
So these are the two qualities, these are the two reactions, shall we say, which we are getting in touch with when we bring somebody to mind who's hurt us.

138
00:30:44,006 --> 00:30:48,050
So again, be careful not to let the mind wander off into a fantasy.

139
00:30:48,632 --> 00:30:52,938
Just hold the image fairly still and just feel.

140
00:30:52,998 --> 00:30:57,403
Allow the heart to express its turbulences.

141
00:30:59,125 --> 00:31:00,267
Open up to the heart.

142
00:31:00,871 --> 00:31:03,208
with affectionate awareness.

143
00:31:05,162 --> 00:31:06,712
Someone who's hurt us

144
00:31:46,332 --> 00:31:53,115
Can we accept that these feelings, these mental states have been produced by us, not the other person?

145
00:31:53,817 --> 00:31:56,045
We're the ones who reacted with hurt.

146
00:31:56,065 --> 00:31:58,231
We're the ones who are seeking revenge.

147
00:32:17,045 --> 00:32:22,730
And we accept that these are unwholesome states, unskillful, just making us suffer.

148
00:32:42,153 --> 00:32:45,297
So the antidote, of course, is to forgive.

149
00:32:46,153 --> 00:32:50,663
So we bring this person to mind and have a conversation with them.

150
00:32:50,683 --> 00:32:53,108
Just tell them how much you were hurt, etc.

151
00:32:53,169 --> 00:32:56,936
How you do not intend to seek revenge and all that.

152
00:32:57,939 --> 00:33:00,805
And finally tell them that you forgive them.

153
00:33:38,752 --> 00:33:41,844
Perhaps you can see in them a desire to be reconciled.

154
00:33:43,048 --> 00:33:46,077
And they also want to make friends, make amends.

155
00:33:47,502 --> 00:33:49,589
Can you hold out to hand a friendship to them?

156
00:34:11,338 --> 00:34:12,380
Can you wish them well?

157
00:34:25,264 --> 00:34:29,331
And again, allowing that image to fade away.

158
00:34:39,605 --> 00:35:01,561
turning to ourselves and the harm that we might have done ourselves physically mentally so there are two contemplations which help us here the first is dependence origination the psychology the Buddha teaches and a teaching on karma so

159
00:35:02,909 --> 00:35:28,494
understanding dependent origination means that we understand that we have started from a position of not knowing and we make a mistake and this mistake leads us to have wrong attitude wrong understandings and through the practice of meditation these are corrected and we end up with wisdom

160
00:35:30,802 --> 00:35:54,161
from the heart's point of view we're never meant to do any harm we begin from a place of innocence but because of these wrong understandings we do harm and that's the suffering that we have within us and the pain that we cause others and through the process of meditation we allow the heart to heal itself

161
00:35:54,597 --> 00:36:23,018
and so we end up with purity so there's your two trajectories from ignorance from not knowing it's not a culpable ignorance you just we just didn't know from a mistake a delusion through these misunderstandings we create attitudes and then through the meditation through insight we begin to undo these knots and we become wise

162
00:36:23,807 --> 00:36:49,494
from the heart's point of view we begin with innocence but because of these wrong understandings we create harm to ourselves to others and through the process of meditation we allow the heart to heal itself and we end with purity so we're on the back end of this we're moving now very rapidly towards wisdom and purity

163
00:36:51,972 --> 00:36:53,353
Karma is very simple.

164
00:36:53,414 --> 00:36:57,518
It's at an obvious base.

165
00:36:57,539 --> 00:37:00,481
When you do harm, harm comes of it.

166
00:37:00,561 --> 00:37:05,447
And when you do something that's wholesome, good, good comes to it.

167
00:37:05,467 --> 00:37:08,070
You can say that as a sort of general rule.

168
00:37:09,233 --> 00:37:19,465
From our point of view, with this forgiveness, we have to understand that punishment, self-hatred, self-aversion,

169
00:37:19,985 --> 00:37:23,128
picking on ourselves are completely unnecessary.

170
00:37:23,929 --> 00:37:28,134
Whenever we do harm, all we have to do is bear the consequence.

171
00:37:28,153 --> 00:37:28,675
That's enough.

172
00:37:29,295 --> 00:37:35,141
That's the karmic consequence of what we've done.

173
00:37:35,181 --> 00:37:44,813
So we don't have to get into all this other stuff about hating ourselves and punishing ourselves or even, and of course, punishing others.

174
00:37:45,954 --> 00:37:48,016
So it really is all about

175
00:37:48,385 --> 00:38:17,126
receiving the consequences of unwholesome action so can we uh choose something that we've done to ourselves which has harmed us it might be physically physical harm we might take them drugs or whatever it might be emotional harm we might have put things in our minds which have become obsessive you know just choose one of them

176
00:38:25,273 --> 00:38:26,817
Now can you open up to that?

177
00:38:27,599 --> 00:38:28,842
Can you receive it?

178
00:38:30,846 --> 00:38:35,596
Can you hold it with a sense of care, of loving kindness?

179
00:38:38,862 --> 00:38:40,987
And just allow it to manifest.

180
00:38:59,952 --> 00:39:02,219
Now you can also talk to your body.

181
00:39:02,259 --> 00:39:03,802
You can talk to your heart.

182
00:39:07,974 --> 00:39:10,603
You can speak gently into your heart.

183
00:39:40,282 --> 00:39:46,871
Sometimes if you have the time, you wait for the heart to completely express its emotional turbulence.

184
00:39:48,192 --> 00:39:52,237
It might be feeling sorry about any harm you've done to your body.

185
00:39:52,277 --> 00:39:59,304
You might be angry about the way you've behaved in the past and things like that.

186
00:40:04,570 --> 00:40:06,813
So for the purpose of this exercise,

187
00:40:07,300 --> 00:40:11,302
It's a case of making a resolution that you won't behave like that again.

188
00:40:12,483 --> 00:40:14,846
To seal the past with the resolution.

189
00:40:33,561 --> 00:40:37,105
Now if it's a habit that we don't want and we keep falling into it,

190
00:40:37,742 --> 00:41:06,297
and we have to recognize that sometimes one resolution won't do and we have to go through this many times until we disempower a habit we don't want and offer ourselves some blessings

191
00:41:31,168 --> 00:41:34,193
So this brings to an end our practice of loving kindness.

192
00:41:35,594 --> 00:41:41,583
And we can move to just an exercise which helps us to develop determination.

193
00:41:43,125 --> 00:41:46,048
So there are four steps to this.

194
00:41:46,128 --> 00:41:47,409
First of all, I can.

195
00:41:48,170 --> 00:41:53,277
So I can resist temptation and I can develop virtue.

196
00:41:54,489 --> 00:41:58,297
Then we have to take on personal responsibility for this.

197
00:41:58,577 --> 00:42:02,423
I ought to, for my own benefit and the benefit of others.

198
00:42:03,887 --> 00:42:06,711
Sometimes you have to cajole, you have to encourage the heart.

199
00:42:06,911 --> 00:42:08,315
I want to, I want to.

200
00:42:09,737 --> 00:42:15,447
And finally, when the occasion arises, I will, I will resist that temptation.

201
00:42:16,389 --> 00:42:18,152
I will develop that virtue.

202
00:42:20,139 --> 00:42:27,289
Can we bring to mind a trait within our characters, personalities, which we would be very happy to be rid of?

203
00:42:35,539 --> 00:42:40,105
And then just gently speaking again, always speaking into the heart, you see.

204
00:42:42,226 --> 00:42:44,150
I can resist.

205
00:42:44,990 --> 00:42:48,335
I ought to for my own benefit and the benefit of others.

206
00:42:48,976 --> 00:42:50,097
I want to.

207
00:42:50,650 --> 00:42:55,695
And I will, can, ought, want and will.

208
00:42:56,639 --> 00:42:57,402
Three times.

209
00:43:59,280 --> 00:44:02,706
We can bring a virtue to mind that we'd like to develop more.

210
00:44:11,782 --> 00:44:18,414
So I can, I ought to, want to, and I will when the occasion arises.

211
00:44:20,297 --> 00:44:21,340
Three times.

212
00:45:06,577 --> 00:45:12,407
Well, this brings to an end our little practices of developing determination.

213
00:45:13,190 --> 00:45:19,581
So we can end this now with a slightly different way of developing metta, just repeating these phrases.

214
00:45:23,688 --> 00:45:27,675
May I be free of greed and selfishness.

215
00:45:33,882 --> 00:45:37,226
May I be free of anger and ill will.

216
00:45:44,275 --> 00:45:48,039
May I be free of fear and anxiety.

217
00:45:55,568 --> 00:45:58,692
May I be free of ignorance and delusion.

218
00:46:05,067 --> 00:46:19,400
May I be kind and gentle, sympathetic and benevolent.

219
00:46:19,420 --> 00:46:23,110
May I be forgiving and compassionate.

220
00:46:30,615 --> 00:46:35,061
May I be joyful and rejoice in the success of others.

221
00:46:44,072 --> 00:46:47,077
May I be peace loving and calm.

222
00:46:54,347 --> 00:46:57,771
May I be liberated of all my sufferings.

223
00:47:06,070 --> 00:47:20,550
